  "prompt": "How is Heaven described according the Bible?",
  "response": "According to the Bible, Heaven is described in various ways:\n\n1. Physical Description\n- A place of great beauty and light\n- Streets of gold (Revelation 21:21)\n- Pearly gates and walls of precious stones (Revelation 21:18-21)\n- A city with twelve foundations (Revelation 21:14)\n\n2. Spiritual Characteristics\n- God's dwelling place\n- A realm of perfect peace and joy\n- No more suffering, pain, or death (Revelation 21:4)\n- Presence of God and Jesus Christ\n- Eternal life for believers\n\n3. Relational Aspects\n- A place of reunion with saved loved ones\n- Worship and praise of God\n- Fellowship with other believers\n- Absence of sin and evil\n\n4. Key Passages\n- John 14:2 - \"In my Father's house are many rooms\"\n- Revelation 21-22 - Detailed descriptions of the New Jerusalem\n- 1 Corinthians 2:9 - \"No eye has seen... what God has prepared for those who love him\"\n\n5. Theological Understanding\n- Reserved for those who believe in Jesus Christ\n- Entered through faith and salvation\n- A perfect, eternal dwelling place for God's people\n\nThe biblical descriptions emphasize Heaven as a place of ultimate peace, joy, and communion with God.",
